    <div type="definition">
        <!-- PREMIS Definition -->
        <p>The size in bytes of the file or bitstream stored in the repository.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="rationale">
        <!-- PREMIS Rationale -->
        <p>Size is useful for ensuring the correct number of bytes from storage has
            been retrieved and that an application has enough room to move or
            process files. It might also be used when billing for storage.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div type="usagenotes">
        <!-- PREMIS Usage notes -->
        <p>Defining this semantic unit as size in bytes makes it unnecessary to
            record a unit of measurement. However, for the purpose of data exchange
            the unit of measurement should be stated or understood by both
            partners.</p>
    </div>
    
